  "caption": "🗼Can I complete 50 Tokyo Bucket List items in 5 days!?\n\nThis is Day 2 and we did 13 things!!!! so I’m ahead 😆 \n\nthank you @caspace_official for gifting me a new phone case! they’re my fav 💙\n\nfollow me @ebifried_ for Day 3 of doing 50 things in Tokyo hehe 🤭\n\n#tokyotravel #traveljapan #japantravel #harajuku",
  "transcript": "japan only has five weekends left before tourism takes over but i still have 50 things to do so here's day two of me trying to get through everything starting off with a viral brunch i've always wanted to try this and yes it kind of lives up to the hype but i do wish they had indoor seating then i wanted to do brandy melville as soon as it opens because otherwise there's lines just to go inside next door is streamer coffee it's actually quite hard to get good coffee in tokyo and this one is pretty expensive but it's so good next was caspase it's a viral phone case store the designs are so cute and make for perfect souvenirs i finally got to visit the mopusan flagship store everything is exclusive but all the keychains were sold out then we checked out candy stripper it's one of my favorite japanese brands half of the place was on sale then instead of sitting down for lunch i wanted to show my friend the best fries in tokyo but it was kind of meth today so then we went to rumble crumble because i'm also looking for the best cookie in tokyo but i don't think these are for me then we walked off the food to pam i've seen it on social media lately it's a really unique store set in a japanese house and i think it's such a cute way to see what traditional houses in japan are like and now time for the most overwhelming part of harajuku the famous takeshitadori it's so packed on weekends but i wanted to check out the new sanrio store and it was worth it there was lots of cute new merch finally went to at the kosme also way too crowded on weekends but i wanted to treat myself to some skincare i've been wanting these for years it was dinner time and we had italy which is right next door it's quite famous for having authentic italian food but i would still categorize it as japanese pasta it was such a productive day we did 13 things only me to do the rest",
